    IComponent, IEndOfDayPerformer, IExceptionListener, IFIXListener, IFIXMessageProcessor, IFIXSource, ILink, IHasAttributes, IConfigurable, IRegisterable, IMessageListener, IMessageProcessor, IMessageSource, ICatalysEventListener, Cloneable, EventListener

    public class LinkBase
extends FIXSourceListenerBase
implements ILink
    Default implementation of ILink.

    Filters out logon/logout messages.

    This message processor sets the storeMessages attribute to false to enable message reuse.

      • isConcurrentRouting

        public boolean isConcurrentRouting()
        Description copied from interface: ILink
        If true, multiple sessions are allowed to route messages concurrently (i.e. in different threads), potentially to the same target session. This allows for more efficient processing but requires care with the implementation of message processors in the processing chain of the target sessions due to potential thread-safety issues. It false, only one session may route messages to another session at a time. This easier to implement, but it is possible for a sluggish target session to slow down the routing of other sessions.
        Specified by:
        isConcurrentRouting in interface ILink
        Returns:
        Whether the routing is concurrent or serial
